  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\n`crypto/bls` crate supports two external crates for BLS signatures operations: `blst` and `milagro_bls`. `blst` is used by default and `milagro_bls` is optional. However, the current implementation implies that even though `milagro_bls` is used, `blst` will be compiled and included in the `bls` library. \r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nRust version: 1.62.0\r\nLighthouse version: `unstable` branch, at https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/commit/25f0e261cb37ca1945c7ec581da0c7cf09ad4c95\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\n`blst` crate dependency is not optional, included by default, even if the crate is compiled with `--no-default-features` flag and `milagro_bls` feature.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\n`blst` crate dependency is optional but included by default. When `--no-default-features` flag and `milagro_bls` feature are applied, only `milagro_bls` crate is included for BLS signatures.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\n* make `blst` crate `optional`\r\n* include `blst` dependency into `supranational` feature\r\n* hide `blst`-related code with `supranational` feature\r\n",
